File: President Cyril Ramaphosa. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - South Africa moves to lockdown alert level 3 at midnight. President Cyril Ramaphosa made the announcement on Tuesday. The curfew will now begin at 10 pm, ending at 4 am. The President announced that Public gatherings will now be restricted to 50 people indoors and 100 people outdoors. READ: WATCH | President Ramaphosa addresses the nation Off-site sales of alcohol will be restricted between Monday and Thursday. Meanwhile, the on-site sales at restaurants remain as per their liquor licenses.